  plantName: Birch Tree
  description: A birch tree is a thin-leaved, deciduous hardwood tree belonging to
    the genus Betula and the family Betulaceae. Known for their distinctive paper-like
    bark that often peels in thin, horizontal layers, they are fast-growing, short-lived
    pioneer species common across the Northern Hemisphere's temperate and boreal
    regions.
